> user
Many of the tests are not returning early after success comparison. This causes typing errors
since the ResultType is a discriminative union.

For example:
``` ts
expect(r.success).toBe(true);
expect(r.result.nodes.map((n:any)=>n.path)).toEqual([
    '/docs/alice-doc',
    '/docs/shared',
]);
```

should be written like
``` ts
expect(r.success).toBe(true);
if(!r.success){return}
expect(r.result.nodes.map((n:any)=>n.path)).toEqual([
    '/docs/alice-doc',
    '/docs/shared',
]);
```

